== Births == * [[Shōō (Kamakura period)|Shōō]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1288]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Later Fushimi Tennō|ja|後伏見天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 93rd {{ill|Emperor of Japan|ja|天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} (died [[1336]]). * [[Tenbun]] 18th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1549]] {{ill|March 31|ja|3月31日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tsuchi no Junkei|ja|筒井順慶|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Sengoku daimyō (died [[1584]]). * {{ill|Kannen|ja|寛延|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1749]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōta Nan-Ō|ja|大田南畝|12=draft|12=draft}}, a playwright (died [[1823]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1825]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shiranui Kōuenemon|ja|不知火光右ヱ門|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th Yokozuna (died [[1879]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1832]] {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsunomon Sansōko|ja|松の門三艸子|12=draft|12=draft}}, a waka poet and geisha (died [[1914]]). * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1849]] {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hirata Tōsuke|ja|平田東助|12=draft|12=draft}}, a bureaucrat and politician (died [[1925]]). * 嘉永4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1851]] {{ill|April 4|ja|4月4日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ogino Ginko|ja|荻野吟子|12=draft|12=draft}}, a feminist and Japan’s first female doctor (died [[1913]]). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1855]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Sugiura Shigetake|ja|杉浦重剛|12=draft|12=draft}}, a thinker and educator (died [[1924]]). * 安政6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1859]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Yasui Rimin|ja|安井理民|12=draft|12=draft}}, founder of the first Sōbu Railway (died [[1894]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Itaya Hazan|ja|板谷波山|12=draft|12=draft}}, a ceramic artist (died [[1963]]).
== Deaths == * [[Tenbun]] 20th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1551]] {{ill|April 8|ja|4月8日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Oda Nobuhide|ja|織田信秀|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and father of Oda Nobunaga (born [[1510]]). * [[Keichō]] 4th year (leap March) ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1599]] {{ill|April 27|ja|4月27日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Maeda Toshiie|ja|前田利家|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and one of the Tairō; he was the first lord of the Kaga Domain (born [[1538]]). * 安政7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} 1860, {{ill|March 24|ja|3月24日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ii Naosuke|ja|井伊直弼|12=draft|12=draft}}, Tairō of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[1815]]). * 慶応4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} 1868, {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Sagara Sōzō|ja|相楽総三|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Sonnō jōi activist (born [[1839]]).
== Commemorations == * {{ill|Shōmiji|ja|上巳|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hina Matsuri|ja|雛祭り|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hama-ori|ja|浜下り|12=draft|12=draft}} – In Okinawa, women purify themselves by presenting food in tiered boxes at the beach; this tradition is combined with clam digging. * 玄天上帝誕辰 – The birthday celebration of the Taoist deity {{ill|Xuantian Shangdi|ja|玄天上帝|12=draft|12=draft}}. * A traditional event of the Zhuang people in China (in Zhuang language: samnyiedcosam) to honor their ancestors, accompanied by large-scale singing gatherings. * An independent New Year celebration by the Khor Lao ethnic group in Vietnam.
