{{citation needed|March 7 (Lunisolar)}}

{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 7''' is the 7th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1583]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日}}) – {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|羽柴秀吉}} (later known as {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉}}) caused the fall of {{ill|Kashida Katsuie|ja|柴田勝家}}’s forces by capturing the castle at {{ill|Ise Province|ja|伊勢}}’s {{ill|Kameyama Castle (Ise Province)|ja|亀山城 (伊勢国)}} in a prelude to the {{ill|Battle of Shizugatake|ja|賤ヶ岳の戦い}}. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1603]] {{ill|April 14|ja|4月14日}}) – {{ill|Nihonbashi|ja|日本橋}} in Chūō, Tokyo, was opened. * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永}} 19th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1642]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日}}) – The {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|徳川幕府}} established the office of {{ill|Kanjō Bugyō|ja|勘定奉行}}. * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永}} 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1854]] {{ill|March 31|ja|3月31日}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate and U.S. envoy Perry signed the {{ill|Nippon-America Treaty|ja|日米和親条約}} (Kanagawa Treaty) in Yokohama, ending Japan’s national seclusion. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1860]] {{ill|March 24|ja|3月24日}}) – During the [[Sakuradamon Incident|桜田門外の変]], Tairō {{ill|Ii Naosuke|ja|井伊直弼}} was attacked and killed by rōnin outside Sakurada Gate of Edo Castle. * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1868]] {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日}}) – The Higashiyama Road Vanguard Government executed officials, including members of the {{ill|Akahōtai|ja|赤報隊}}, as pseudo-officials.
