== Commemorations ==
* {{ill|Shōmiji|ja|上巳|qq=|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hina Matsuri|ja|雛祭り|qq=|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Hama-ori|ja|浜下り|qq=|12=draft}} – In Okinawa, women purify themselves by presenting food in tiered boxes at the beach; this tradition is combined with clam digging.
* 玄天上帝誕辰 – The birthday celebration of the Taoist deity {{ill|Xuantian Shangdi|ja|玄天上帝|qq=|12=draft}}.
* A traditional event of the Zhuang people in China (in Zhuang language: samnyiedcosam) to honor their ancestors, accompanied by large-scale singing gatherings.
* An independent New Year celebration by the Khor Lao ethnic group in Vietnam.


