'''March 7''' is the 7th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1583]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|羽柴秀吉|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} (later known as {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) caused the fall of {{ill|Kashida Katsuie|ja|柴田勝家|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}’s forces by capturing the castle at {{ill|Ise Province|ja|伊勢|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}’s {{ill|Kameyama Castle (Ise Province)|ja|亀山城 (伊勢国)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} in a prelude to the {{ill|Battle of Shizugatake|ja|賤ヶ岳の戦い|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1603]] {{ill|April 14|ja|4月14日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Nihonbashi|ja|日本橋|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} in Chūō, Tokyo, was opened.
* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 19th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1642]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|徳川幕府|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} established the office of {{ill|Kanjō Bugyō|ja|勘定奉行|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1854]] {{ill|March 31|ja|3月31日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate and U.S. envoy Perry signed the {{ill|Nippon-America Treaty|ja|日米和親条約|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} (Kanagawa Treaty) in Yokohama, ending Japan’s national seclusion.
* {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1860]] {{ill|March 24|ja|3月24日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the [[Sakuradamon Incident|桜田門外の変]], Tairō {{ill|Ii Naosuke|ja|井伊直弼|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} was attacked and killed by rōnin outside Sakurada Gate of Edo Castle.
* {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Higashiyama Road Vanguard Government executed officials, including members of the {{ill|Akahōtai|ja|赤報隊|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, as pseudo-officials.

